                <div class= "col-6">
                    <div class= "overflow-hidden d-block" style= "height: 100px;">
                        <p class= "py-1">This is an example of using <span class= "text-danger">.overflow-hidden</span> on an element with set width and height dimensions. By design, this content will vertically scroll.</p>
                        <p class= "py-1">This is an example of using <span class= "text-danger">.overflow-hidden</span> on an element with set width and height dimensions. By design, this content will vertically scroll.</p>
                    </div>
